&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for one Consultant Clinical Haematology post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mid and South Essex (MSE) NHS Foundation Trust is recruiting for a consultant to join our team. This post is based at the Broomfield Hospital, Chelmsford site and would suit either an established consultant looking for new challenges, or a fellowship trained CCT holder looking for a first consultant post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work in close collaboration with our sister haematology departments at Basildon and Southend hospitals. Both departments operate at level 2a offering treatment for lymphomas and leukaemia. There are plans for subspecialisation at all 3 sites with emphasis on service development in line with academic and population needs. Several subspecialty subgroups are created such as Sickle, Thrombosis, laboratory, myeloma etc with representation from all sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in joining this new and innovative team, please follow the links below; we would welcome your application. Further information can be gained from:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Waseem Nagi; Group Clinical Lead – Clinical Haematology; Waseem.nagi@meht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Faisal bin Reza; Group Clinical Director – Pathology Services; Faisal.bin-reza@btuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CLOSING DATE: 4 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
